VERSION 1
WHEN PRESENT (?i)\bSELECT\s+(password|ssn|creditcard|api_key|token|pin)\s+FROM\s+[^\s]+\b
WHEN EXPR MISSING:example|sample|dummy|test|placeholder
REPORT AS area_of_interest
REASON Detects SQL statements querying sensitive data directly, which could expose data if logs or exceptions are mishandled.
TRACE Externalized rule logic for SQL Query: Querying Sensitive Information Directly in Code.
